Theodoor Gerard van Lidth de Jeude (8 July 1788 in Tiel - 
23 December 1863 in Utrecht) was a Dutch physician, veterinarian,
 and zoologist and was the first director of the newly establ
 ished Rijks Veterinary College where Veterinary medicine was first
  taught in the Netherlands in late 1821. 



  
His primary contribution to science was the collecting of specimens.[1]